subject: Leave the option to ops for new features
revisions:
[{'number': 2, 'created': '2017-09-28 01:21:51.000000000', 'files': ['neutron_vpnaas_dashboard/dashboards/project/vpn/tabs.py'], 'message': 'Leave the option to ops for new features

Currently, in our public cloud (Catalyst Cloud based in New Zealand), we
are running an old Liberty Neutron version which is missing the endpoint
group support for VPNaaS. But we're runnning Horizon Ocata and going to
migrate to Horizon Pike. In our testing, the new support of endpoint group
in VPN dashboard will throw an error say the endpoint group API is not
found, which is correct. But it would be nice to leave an option for
cloud ops to "disable" a new feature temporarily. This patch is adding a
new config options for VPN service to fix above issue and benefit any
similar issue in the future.

Change-Id: I3d94cb3a6cf81d5ce0c7c11efb1d5ad80ec090e9
'}]
commit_message:
Leave the option to ops for new features

Currently, in our public cloud (Catalyst Cloud based in New Zealand), we
are running an old Liberty Neutron version which is missing the endpoint
group support for VPNaaS. But we're runnning Horizon Ocata and going to
migrate to Horizon Pike. In our testing, the new support of endpoint group
in VPN dashboard will throw an error say the endpoint group API is not
found, which is correct. But it would be nice to leave an option for
cloud ops to "disable" a new feature temporarily. This patch is adding a
new config options for VPN service to fix above issue and benefit any
similar issue in the future.

Change-Id: I3d94cb3a6cf81d5ce0c7c11efb1d5ad80ec090e9

subject: update ref search logic for zuulv3 CI layout
revisions:
[{'number': 2, 'created': '2017-09-28 21:55:39.000000000', 'files': ['reno/scanner.py', 'reno/tests/test_scanner.py'], 'message': "update ref search logic for zuulv3 CI layout

If the reference points explicitly to the origin remote, but that
remote isn't present (as it won't be when zuul configures the repo in
CI), then we want the shortened form of the reference. We put this
option last in the list because we want the more explicit name to be
used when someone is running reno locally with a more standard git
configuration.

Change-Id: I1fef83e95b0a0605db7e59676561bf1396e799e6
Signed-off-by: Doug Hellmann <doug@doughellmann.com>
"}]
commit_message:
update ref search logic for zuulv3 CI layout

If the reference points explicitly to the origin remote, but that
remote isn't present (as it won't be when zuul configures the repo in
CI), then we want the shortened form of the reference. We put this
option last in the list because we want the more explicit name to be
used when someone is running reno locally with a more standard git
configuration.

Change-Id: I1fef83e95b0a0605db7e59676561bf1396e799e6
Signed-off-by: Doug Hellmann <doug@doughellmann.com>

commit_message:
Update all instances when their AZ is renamed

When AZ is renamed, the 'availability_zone' property of the instances in
this AZ is not updated and certain operations doesn't work on them
(resize, migrate). This patch fixes this by updating the instance
property everytime when AZ is renamed.

Change-Id: Icf58b0fd2e1d77abb817ea46f188f386863578d0
Closes-Bug: #1378904

commit_message:
Fixed creation neutron api mapping for security groups

Fixed creation of security group and security group rule via
neutronclient api mapping.
There was a switch from novaclient to neutronclient
for creating a security groups and rules in change
5d5666b10e57a94bcde06c8a296002175d935c7b but
the argument mapping for this function has not been changed.

Change-Id: I1774b73c61adb3b44a61f3f56f99e85f278deb83
Closes-Bug: 1716922

Fix all Url fields for new spec-cleaner release

It must be "URL" instead of "Url" now[1].

[1] https://github.com/openSUSE/spec-cleaner/commit/a82a7330980af

subject: report incorrect matches for tests
revisions:
[{'number': 4, 'created': '2017-09-20 18:48:55.000000000', 'files': ['whereto/tests/test_app.py', 'whereto/app.py'], 'message': 'report incorrect matches for tests

Report the redirects that result from a test that does not produce the
expected value so it is easier to debug which rule is matching and
why.

At the same time, create a function to report errors from the common
data structures and reuse it instead of repeating the looping pattern
several times.

Change-Id: Ic540e658625285c8861b5da9844317153957a4dd
Signed-off-by: Doug Hellmann <doug@doughellmann.com>
'}]
commit_message:
report incorrect matches for tests

Report the redirects that result from a test that does not produce the
expected value so it is easier to debug which rule is matching and
why.

At the same time, create a function to report errors from the common
data structures and reuse it instead of repeating the looping pattern
several times.

Change-Id: Ic540e658625285c8861b5da9844317153957a4dd
Signed-off-by: Doug Hellmann <doug@doughellmann.com>

commit_message:
Replace default subnetpool API tests with UT

As existence of default subnetpool is required for auto allocated tests
and other tests in Nova, it is created by devstack. Default subnetpool
API tests perform create operations and tests are skipped in case
default subnetpool already exsits in the system.

This patch replaces coverage of skipped API tests, that are never run on
the gate, with unittests using extension testing.

Change-Id: I04986aaf06525db45290b0b838cc491ee99b751f

commit_message:
iso8601.is8601.Utc No Longer Exists

iso8601.UTC is correct datetime UTC field object.
iso8601 >= 0.1.12 includes only iso8601.UTC for python3
while both UTC and Utc() for python2. Less then 0.1.12
included both UTC and Utc() for both python2/3.

Change-Id: I9b2a8ba5a5ab44c95e68d67e0e3ee8e2c0024b03
Closes-Bug: #1715486

subject: Don't iterate through addresses in netaddr.IPNetwork
reviewers: [{'_account_id': 3, 'name': 'Jenkins', 'username': 'jenkins'}, {'_account_id': 6928, 'name': 'Ben Nemec', 'email': 'openstack@nemebean.com', 'username': 'bnemec'}, {'_account_id': 9656, 'name': 'Ihar Hrachyshka', 'email': 'ihrachys@redhat.com', 'username': 'ihrachys', 'status': 'Red Hat Networking Systems Engineer'}]
revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2017-09-05 11:58:24.000000000', 'files': ['oslo_serialization/tests/test_jsonutils.py', 'oslo_serialization/jsonutils.py'], 'message': "Don't iterate through addresses in netaddr.IPNetwork

Currently, to_primitive tries to iterate through all addresses in the
network, because the type doesn't have a special handling that would
short curcuit it, but also has __iter__. This may be detrimental to
performance, up to the point of node crash due to memory exhaustion if
the passed network range is too large (think of 0.0.0.0/0 or even
2001::/64). This behavior also makes it impossible to restore the
original data format (CIDR).

This patch short curcuits the iteration by handling the IPNetwork type
as a special case, same as we do for IPAddress.

Change-Id: I6aecd2d057d282a655ff9e4918c164253142b188
Closes-Bug: #1698355
(cherry picked from commit 38ac21b523f23f802557d94b527821bc84deaa16)
"}]
commit_message:
Don't iterate through addresses in netaddr.IPNetwork

Currently, to_primitive tries to iterate through all addresses in the
network, because the type doesn't have a special handling that would
short curcuit it, but also has __iter__. This may be detrimental to
performance, up to the point of node crash due to memory exhaustion if
the passed network range is too large (think of 0.0.0.0/0 or even
2001::/64). This behavior also makes it impossible to restore the
original data format (CIDR).

This patch short curcuits the iteration by handling the IPNetwork type
as a special case, same as we do for IPAddress.

Change-Id: I6aecd2d057d282a655ff9e4918c164253142b188
Closes-Bug: #1698355
(cherry picked from commit 38ac21b523f23f802557d94b527821bc84deaa16)

Community has decided to do not translate log messages anymore.
The motivation behind removing translation jobs for log messages
is that when operators encounters any unfamiliar situations(e.g.

commit_message:
Hacking: do not translate log messages

Community has decided to do not translate log messages anymore.
The motivation behind removing translation jobs for log messages
is that when operators encounters any unfamiliar situations(e.g.
nova error, keystone error etc.), searching on the Internet
based on actual log content would have more results than searching
translated log messages.

In this patch I have added hacking rule to check that logs are
not translated.

Change-Id: I90d53d617aac6839c2f2ab119847cbf24a1300e0

commit_message:
Inspection Mechanism For Capacity Limited Host

Cinder now has a scheduler filter called "CapacityFilter" which
allow users to create volume under capacity limit. But some
APIs which don't go through cinder-scheduler will break the
destination host's capacity.
So we should add the check mechanism for these APIs.

Change-Id: I5d7a8bcd621c5584f86499dcc6a2ff5298ed47a8
bp: inspection-mechanism-for-capacity-limited-host

[{'number': 14, 'created': '2017-09-26 02:23:17.000000000', 'files': ['specs/queens/report-backend-state-in-service-list.rst'], 'message': "Report backend state in service list

Currently, Cinder couldn't report backend state
to service, operators only know that cinder-volume
process is up, but isn't aware of if the backend
storage device is ok. Users still can create volume
and go to fail over and over again.

This bp propose to get the backend state from driver
and record it into scheduler, operators or management
system could query this via service list.

Change-Id: I99fb91e44104f5570bb533103f445738800c164b
Implements: blueprint report-backend-state-in-service-list
"}]
commit_message:
Report backend state in service list

Currently, Cinder couldn't report backend state
to service, operators only know that cinder-volume
process is up, but isn't aware of if the backend
storage device is ok. Users still can create volume
and go to fail over and over again.

This bp propose to get the backend state from driver
and record it into scheduler, operators or management
system could query this via service list.

Change-Id: I99fb91e44104f5570bb533103f445738800c164b
Implements: blueprint report-backend-state-in-service-list

commit_message:
Adds tripleo::network::midonet::insights class

MidoNet Enterprise Manager users can also enable Insights, which enables
them to visualize analytics about the traffic.

Only the negative test is implemented (when `hiera('step') == 3`) since
imlementing the other case would require to add logstash, elasticsearch
and another bunch of dependencies to the Puppetfile. Also tests are
already implemented in the openstack/puppet-midonet module.

Change-Id: I2ac159790860973e43154bc665c4db7335fb2005
Partial-Bug: #1647302

commit_message:

network state database (NSDB). It installs and configures Zookeeper
and Cassandra.

for the openstack/puppet-midonet module, which already includes unit

commit_message:
Add link to OpenStack Charms Deployment Guide

This patch adds a link into the "OpenStack Pike Deployment Guides"
[1] page that points to the "OpenStack Charms Deployment Guide" [2].

The link has been added alphabetically, and this means it sits between
the existing two links.  The patch also corrects some broken HTML in the
files.

[1] https://docs.openstack.org/pike/deploy/
[2] https://docs.openstack.org/charm-deployment-guide/latest/

In 2.47 we introduced inlined flavors, which include extra_specs if so
authorized. The code was doing a policy check deep in the per-instance
handler that generated this blob. For queries with a lot of instances,
this policy check is a lot of overhead, especially as it introduces a
check of the policy file on disk, in case it has changed.

This patch makes us calculate the permission flag once per list operation
and pass it down to the lower layers to honor.

Closes-Bug: #1719966
Change-Id: I036623ae7409c2e6c6a754b4c8d5c9120f777774
(cherry picked from commit b1591d1080e4dbfbaf5351e009efa3abd11d88d4)
'}]
commit_message:
Fix policy check performance in 2.47+

In 2.47 we introduced inlined flavors, which include extra_specs if so
authorized. The code was doing a policy check deep in the per-instance
handler that generated this blob. For queries with a lot of instances,
this policy check is a lot of overhead, especially as it introduces a
check of the policy file on disk, in case it has changed.

This patch makes us calculate the permission flag once per list operation
and pass it down to the lower layers to honor.

Closes-Bug: #1719966
Change-Id: I036623ae7409c2e6c6a754b4c8d5c9120f777774
(cherry picked from commit b1591d1080e4dbfbaf5351e009efa3abd11d88d4)

commit_message:
Update init containers

Previously Kubernetes only supported init containers stored
in json encoded annotations. This PS switches them all to
use the native initContainer yaml section now.

Change-Id: Ib8d7a4581baa01173d420570468687679f433e08

This fixes them to be what they should have been - with the following

commit_message:
Fix bad python35 jobs migration

Something went sideways and standalone python35 jobs got transitioned
non-voting legacy-python35 jobs.

This fixes them to be what they should have been - with the following
logic. If non-voting legacy-python35 exists in both check and gate, then
it was originally voting (because we don't let non-voting things into the
gate normally) If it was only in check, it was non-voting.

We use the templates for this, which is what was originally supposed to
happen.

Change-Id: Iad3af8b526e23bd84db9574a939ad3ecbcef7296

commit_message:
Correctly revoke /etc/sudoers.d/zuul

According to our zuul-worker DIB element the path we want to remove
to revoke zuul sudo access is /etc/sudoers.d/zuul:

http://git.openstack.org/cgit/openstack-infra/project-config/tree/nodepool/elements/zuul-worker/install.d/60-zuul-worker

Generated via:

    sed -i 's/zuul-sudo/zuul/' \
        `git grep --files-with-match '/etc/sudoers.d/zuul-sudo'`

Change-Id: Iea8cf915d815dbf876ca0cee74933f04152395b8

commit_message:
Stop running ansible-lint on playbooks

It can't handle the following form:

  shell:
    cmd: |
      something

Which is both valid and required.

Change-Id: I14896450b16f8e65128804b44a643da63580812d

commit_message:
ovs: log config options when all of them are registered

Otherwise we don't see some of them for the agent, for example,
AGENT.root_helper is missing.

To make sure the logging is as early as possible, and to make sure that
options that may be registered by extensions are also logged, some
refactoring was applied to the code to move the extension manager
loading as early as possible, even before agent's __init__ is called.

Related-Bug: #1718767
Change-Id: I823150cf6406f709d1e4ffa74897d598e80f5329

commit_message:
Add postgresql and gnocchi to OSH

Adds postgresql and gnocchi charts for use with ceilometer. As
postgresql is currently in openstack-helm-addons and we don't have
cross-repo gating yet, this allows us to house these charts until
such gating is in place.

Co-Authored-By: Steve Wilkerson <sw5822@att.com>
Co-Authored-By: Larry Rensing <lr699s@att.com>

Change-Id: I391ef52d3be79aeb84af95cc3100290e751fdc88

subject: Use kolla_internal_vip_address for glance_api servers
revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2017-08-16 08:21:56.000000000', 'files': ['ansible/roles/nova/templates/nova.conf.j2', 'ansible/roles/cinder/templates/cinder.conf.j2'], 'message': 'Use kolla_internal_vip_address for glance_api servers

Nova and Cinder used a list of glance api servers - this list
does not provide a proper high availability because the servers
are connected at random without recalling who is failed last
time. E.g. out of three controllers with a failed first one nova
and cinder can try connection to the first controller because of
random / shuffled choice of the glance server. A proper solution
is to use VIP that connects to alive server from the beginning.
Also as workaround one could significantly increase max number
of retries in configuration files in hope that a random function
will choose a healthy glance server sometime - not a good choice.

Change-Id: Ifaf8ffe3697ec88a6da4c2b43c83975b63dc2e8c
Closes-Bug: #1643509
(cherry picked from commit ac3e4cf9c9b84e43c39cc928ddd1f07687ad2b72)
'}]
commit_message:
Use kolla_internal_vip_address for glance_api servers

Nova and Cinder used a list of glance api servers - this list
does not provide a proper high availability because the servers
are connected at random without recalling who is failed last
time. E.g. out of three controllers with a failed first one nova
and cinder can try connection to the first controller because of
random / shuffled choice of the glance server. A proper solution
is to use VIP that connects to alive server from the beginning.
Also as workaround one could significantly increase max number
of retries in configuration files in hope that a random function
will choose a healthy glance server sometime - not a good choice.

Change-Id: Ifaf8ffe3697ec88a6da4c2b43c83975b63dc2e8c
Closes-Bug: #1643509
(cherry picked from commit ac3e4cf9c9b84e43c39cc928ddd1f07687ad2b72)

commit_message:
Retry container creation in swift

Because of cache management container creation in Swift is somewhat
racy, as we create containers lazily. Work around that issue by retrying
creation a few times.

commit_message:
Config download support for standalone deployments

Presently, "openstack overcloud config download" only supports the
OS::HeatSoftwareDeploymentGroup (plural) resources from deploy-steps.yaml.

This patch adds support to the command to also pull the deployment
resources for each individual server from the OS::Heat::Value resources
called "TripleODeployment", as well as other SoftwareDeploymentGroup
resources not from deploy-steps.j2. See the Depends-On
tripleo-heat-templates patch for how these resources are mapped.

These deployments are applied by additional plays in the generated
playbooks. Instead of having to reimplement each deployment in a native
group:ansible, the ansible tasks just trigger the deployments by calling
55-heat-config remotely with the rendered json deployment data for
whatever deployment is being applied.

This method saves us from having to migrate all these resources to
native ansible (and requring all end users to do so).

Change-Id: I704e877d91fab194179bb930e8e8edd990e4e64c
Depends-On: Ic2af634403b1ab2924c383035f770453f39a2cd5

commit_message:
Config download support for all deployments

Presently, "openstack overcloud config download" only supports the
OS::HeatSoftwareDeploymentGroup (plural) resources from
deploy-steps.yaml.

This patch adds support to the command to also pull the deployment
resources for each individual server from the OS::Heat::Value resources
called "TripleODeployment", as well as other SoftwareDeploymentGroup
resources not from deploy-steps.j2. See the Depends-On
tripleo-heat-templates patch for how these resources are mapped.

These deployments are applied by additional plays in the generated
playbooks. Instead of having to reimplement each deployment in a native
group:ansible, the ansible tasks just trigger the deployments by calling
55-heat-config remotely with the rendered json deployment data for
whatever deployment is being applied.

This method saves us from having to migrate all these resources to
native ansible (and requring all end users to do so).

Also included is a helper script called tripleo-config-download to run
the config download outside of Mistral.

Change-Id: I704e877d91fab194179bb930e8e8edd990e4e64c
Depends-On: Ic2af634403b1ab2924c383035f770453f39a2cd5

commit_message:
Disables port status updates with ODL in HA

ODL enables a feature by default to communicate port state to Neutron
via a websocket connection.  The current implementation does not work in
HA, but does work with a noHA deployment.  Therefore this patch disables
port status for HA deployments only until there is proper support.

Depends-On: I7eb752ad692e5522051f8393376890fcac9a09fe

Closes-Bug: 1718508

Change-Id: I13b5b72285d3c70cdee4d81678470d52be385aaf
Signed-off-by: Tim Rozet <trozet@redhat.com>
(cherry picked from commit 228d7b456c6d5c4958c9add8f9021a83a4360510)

commit_message:
Implement keymgr list() method

Castellan KeyManager has added an abstract list() method starting
in release 0.13.0. We are currently safe since upper constraints
cap it at 0.12.0, but we will want to raise those constraints
soon.

This method isn't actually used in the Nova code, but since it's
an ABC abstract method we must implement it in our ConfKeyMgr. This
just adds a basic skeleton so we don't blow up on missing the method.
Similar fix is proposed to Cinder, see [1]

[1] https://review.openstack.org/#/c/501398/

Change-Id: I70b971b5ba35de4942008f0d72f5b754c37025dc
Closes-bug: #1715451

commit_message:
Add OVN container images to TripleO-common

Prior to this patch, OVN container images were present, but were included
even if OVN services are not enabled. Now the OVN related images are
added and the required parameters are set only if OVN services are enabled.

Change-Id: I6bc03aa65c8401a9e76954c2638006bd28a70482
Partial-bug: #1699085

commit_message:
Install the latest version of setuptools

When trying to install bifrost on CentOS , shade could not be
installed properly, because the system had an old version of
setuptools. Add this upgrade to install-deps, to have the latest
version of it.

commit_message:
docs: installation: remove unnecessary blockquotes

Due to missing spaces, some of the content in the installation
guide is displayed as blockquote without being really quoted
content. This change adds the needed spaces to remove the
generated HTML blockquotes.

The repositories.txt file gets included at different locations
and that file contained the formatting spaces which were needed
from the location which includes that file. It's most of the time
better to do the indentation at the ".. include" level and leave
the file which gets included *without* indentation. Because here,
the indentation in the included file worked for some includes but
not for all, because the content got used at different indentation
levels. That made it necessary to touch the includes in
basic_deployment and post_deployment too.

Follow up patches will deal with the other install guide sections
more in details.

Change-Id: Ie2e7fea6d92f7742d23e22452e394b8ff40975eb
